text: Mulciber strandi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Stephan von Breuning in 1939.BioLib.cz - Mulciber strandi. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It's 23 mm long and 7 mm wide, and its type locality is New Hannover. It was named in honor of Embrik Strand, in whose Festschrift the species description was written. ==References== Category:Homonoeini Category:Beetles described in 1939 Category:Taxa named by Stephan von Breuning
title: Mulciber strandi
